---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Lynn Baxter">
  <main class="container about">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <img class="portrait" src="/assets/portrait.png" alt="Lynn Baxter" width="120" height="120" />
    <div class="prose">
      <p class="lead">I came to design sideways.</p>
      <p>
        I started in biology, detoured through facilities and operations &mdash; the invisible
        machinery that keeps a company running, at Slack and then Blend &mdash; and got handed a
        layoff in 2019 for my trouble. So I retrained at BloomTech and spent 2020 to 2022 designing
        products for fintech and marketplace startups, until life staged a quiet coup: a new baby, a
        decade-deep audiobook habit, and a childcare math problem with no solution. I stepped away
        from the screen. This is me walking back to it, on my own terms.
      </p>
      <p>
        The work itself never changed: find the system that&rsquo;s quietly broken and build the
        thing that should have existed all along. What&rsquo;s particular to me is where I point it
        &mdash; at the problems everyone files under <em>soft</em>. Childhood, care, family. I treat
        them as the hard, high-stakes design problems they actually are, and I hold myself
        responsible for every perspective a tidier solution would rather forget. I&rsquo;d sooner
        make something honest and unfinished than something neat that writes people out.
      </p>
      <p>
        It shows up in whatever medium the problem hands me. When I couldn&rsquo;t find a Dreamlight
        Valley walkthrough that wasn&rsquo;t shrieking at the camera, I made my own &mdash; calm, no
        chatter, something a kid could watch without their nervous system filing a complaint. The
        same reflex runs under Kiddex, and under the childcare space I&rsquo;m designing now. The
        medium changes; the instinct doesn&rsquo;t.
      </p>
      <p>
        I live in Albany, California, helping prop up a blended household of three adults and three
        kids I&rsquo;ve been assembling since 2012. There&rsquo;s a biology degree I never stopped
        thinking with, and a decade of narrating audiobooks &mdash; a children&rsquo;s collection and
        a vampire mystery, because range is the entire point. Someone has to build the calm,
        deliberate version of these things. I&rsquo;d rather it were me &mdash; and I&rsquo;d rather
        it were done well.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    .about { padding-block: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 3rem) clamp(3rem, 8vw, 4rem); max-width: 680px; }
    .portrait { width: 120px; height: 120px; border-radius: 50%; object-fit: cover; margin: 1rem 0 2rem; }
    .prose .lead {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 1.2rem + 1.9vw, 2.1rem);
      font-weight: 500;
      line-height: 1.15;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    }
    .prose p { font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1rem + 0.35vw, 1.15rem); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 1.3rem; max-width: 60ch; color: var(--color-ink); }
    .prose em { font-style: italic; color: var(--color-clay); }
  </style>
</Base>
